  "body": "Hi, I just found out that there are some `Exception` on codes.\r\nMaybe, it's more clarity to use custom exceptions rather than `Exception` ?\r\n\r\n- example\r\n`raise Exception('invalid target name: \"%s\"' % name)` -> `raise InvalidTargetName()`\r\n`raise Exception('Config file \"%s\" does not exist' % config_path)` -> `raise FileNotExist()`\r\n\r\n[code1](https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/blob/c396ee1e3f6bea1cfbe0159302c9391b0811c37c/setup.py#L870)\r\n[code2](https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/blob/c396ee1e3f6bea1cfbe0159302c9391b0811c37c/setup.py#L876)",
