    "body": "@sammiee5311 ðŸ‘‹\r\n\r\n- `setup.py` is the entry of the pyspec build and it's already too long. Personally, I'd like it to be simpler.\r\n    - It could be fine to use some built-in Exceptions. e.g., for your given examples, we can just use [`KeyError`](https://docs.python.org/3/library/exceptions.html#KeyError) and [`FileNotFoundError`](https://docs.python.org/3/library/exceptions.html#FileNotFoundError).\r\n- For testing tools or specs, we now only use custom exceptions for the cases that we want to catch.\r\n    - [`SkippedTest`](https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/blob/cb7c81eb96e9d748abe7248a132423b6326d605a/tests/core/pyspec/eth2spec/gen_helpers/gen_base/gen_runner.py#L174) will be caught in the test runner.\r\n    - #2366 will use `ValidationError` for spec validations. `ValidationError` exceptions will be caught in pyspec tests.\r\n\r\n\r\nIMO, for `setup.py`, we can just use the basic `Exception` or Python built-in exceptions.",
